[hotel]
Guest: Good evening. I have a reservation.
Receptionist: Welcome. May I have your name please?
Guest: My name is John Smith.
Receptionist: Thank you Mr Smith. Here is your room key.

[airport]
Passenger: Good morning. I want to check in.
Staff: May I see your passport?
Passenger: Here you go.
Staff: Thank you. Your gate is A12.

[restaurant]
Customer: Hello, a table for two please.
Waiter: Sure, please follow me.
Customer: Can we see the menu?
Waiter: Of course.

[shopping]
Customer: Excuse me, how much is this?
Shopkeeper: It is twenty dollars.
Customer: Can I get a discount?
Shopkeeper: I can give ten percent.